Package com.netflix.zeno.diff

Class Summary
DiffByteArray Wrapper around a byte array, necessary to implement equals() and hashCode().
DiffFrameworkSerializer Defines operations required to populate inidividual POJO primitive elements into DiffRecords
DiffHeader Header fields for a DiffReport
DiffInstruction The DiffInstruction describes how to derive a DiffReport on the deserialized Objects contained in two FastBlobStateEngines.

In order to perform a diff, we must be able to match up equivalent Objects at the roots of the FastBlobStateEngine.
DiffOperation  
DiffPropertyPath The diff operation must flatten out an object hierarchy into a set of key/value pairs.
DiffRecord A diff record represents the combined values for all fields at all levels in an NFTypeSerializer hierarchy.
DiffRecordValueListMap A map of key/value pairs contained in a DiffRecord.

The DiffRecord flattens out a top-level object into key/value pairs.
DiffReport A diff report is the result of a diff operation.
DiffSerializationFramework This class is used in the context of the Zeno diff operation.
TypeDiff<T> This Object represents the result of a diff for a specific type in the NFTypeSerializer object hierarchy.
TypeDiff.FieldDiff<T>  
TypeDiff.FieldDiffScore<T>  
TypeDiff.ObjectDiffScore<T>  
TypeDiffInstruction<T> The TypeDiffInstruction should be overridden to describe how find matching pairs of Objects of a given type.
TypeDiffOperation<T> This is the main interface for performing a diff between two arbitrary data states.
